history.content:
You can email eecs-inst-support@eecs to find out the status of your application and to see if a particular class has been filled.

We're working on summer hiring right now.  If you are interested in working for a particular course, you may want to contact the

instructor for summer in addition to filing your reader application, since instructors make a lot of the decisions about reader

hiring.  Just tell them, "Hi, I've submitted an application to read for CS x this summer.  I took the class in spring x, and I got an

[A+].  Please let me know if you'd like to know more about me." or something like that.  Don't write a novel; just offer them an

introduction and a way to contact you.  The information is in the application, but the direct contact sometimes works better.
You can email eecs-inst-support@eecs to find out the status of your application and to see if a particular class has been filled.
